      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/logs/agent/sessions/projects/-workspace/memory/MEMORY.md",
        "old_string": "# Django Forms Widget Attribute Escaping Fix\n\n## Issue\nWidget attributes weren't being properly escaped for HTML output when containing special characters like quotes or ampersands.\n\n## Root Cause\nThe Django form templates used the `stringformat` filter when rendering attribute values. The `stringformat` filter is decorated with `@register.filter(is_safe=True)`, which marks the output as safe and prevents Django's auto-escaping from working. This caused unescaped values to appear in HTML attributes, breaking valid HTML when attributes contained quotes or other special characters.\n\n## Solution\nRemoved the `stringformat` filter from Django form templates to allow auto-escaping to work properly:\n1. `/workspace/django/forms/templates/django/forms/attrs.html` - Changed `{{ value|stringformat:'s' }}` to `{{ value }}`\n2. `/workspace/django/forms/templates/django/forms/widgets/attrs.html` - Changed `{{ value|stringformat:'s' }}` to `{{ value }}`\n\nThe Jinja2 templates already had the correct implementation without stringformat.\n\n## Related Components\n- `flatatt()` function in `django/forms/utils.py` - Already properly escapes values using `format_html_join()`\n- Templates in `/django/forms/jinja2/` - Already using correct escaping (no stringformat)",
        "new_string": "# Django Forms Widget Attribute Escaping Fix\n\n## Issue\nWidget attributes and values weren't being properly escaped for HTML output when containing special characters like quotes or ampersands.\n\n## Root Cause\nThe Django form templates used the `stringformat` filter when rendering attribute values and widget values. The `stringformat` filter is decorated with `@register.filter(is_safe=True)`, which marks the output as safe and prevents Django's auto-escaping from working. This caused unescaped values to appear in HTML, breaking valid HTML when values contained quotes or other special characters.\n\n## Solution\nRemoved the `stringformat` filter from Django form templates to allow auto-escaping to work properly:\n1. `/workspace/django/forms/templates/django/forms/attrs.html` - Changed `{{ value|stringformat:'s' }}` to `{{ value }}`\n2. `/workspace/django/forms/templates/django/forms/widgets/attrs.html` - Changed `{{ value|stringformat:'s' }}` to `{{ value }}`\n3. `/workspace/django/forms/templates/django/forms/widgets/input.html` - Changed `{{ widget.value|stringformat:'s' }}` to `{{ widget.value }}`\n4. `/workspace/django/forms/templates/django/forms/widgets/select_option.html` - Changed `{{ widget.value|stringformat:'s' }}` to `{{ widget.value }}`\n\nThese changes bring Django templates into alignment with the Jinja2 templates, which already omit the stringformat filter and properly handle auto-escaping.\n\n## Benefits\n- Widget attribute values with special characters (\", &, <, >) are now properly HTML-escaped\n- mark_safe'd values are still preserved (not re-escaped)\n- Consistent behavior across Django and Jinja2 template engines\n- Non-string values are properly converted to strings by Django's template engine\n\n## Related Components\n- `flatatt()` function in `django/forms/utils.py` - Already properly escapes values using `format_html_join()`\n- Jinja2 templates in `/django/forms/jinja2/` - Already correct (no stringformat)",
